“We are at the junction where this small stream called West Fork comes through this narrow canyon and joins Oak Creek,” Babbitt said as he walked along the trail.
He would introduce himself and ask where they were from, what brought them to Oak Creek and why they like the area.
Whenever he comes back to Arizona, Babbitt said, he feels inundated with memories and nostalgia.
“Here I am in the seventh inning of life, kind of reimmersing in Arizona,” Babbitt said.
Bruce Babbitt and his wife, Hattie Babbitt, hike across the West Fork of Oak Creek near Sedona.